### Issue Details

Currently, this Caddyfile configuration does not throw an error or warning during startup:

```Caddyfile
:8080 {
	file_server {
		root ./cmd
		browse
		hide cobra*
		hide main.go
	}
}
```

The first `hide cobra*` will be effectivly overwritten by `hide main.go`. Files such as "cobra.go" will be shown in the file listing. That's not good.

I think it would be even better, if `hide` can be used legitimately multiple times as this would allow that a snippet of common hides can be used and extended like this use case:


```Caddyfile

(snippet_hide_common) {
	hide *.bak *.swp
}

:8080 {
	handle_path /case1/* {
		file_server {
			root ./cmd
			browse
			import snippet_hide_common
		}
	}

	handle_path /case2/* {
		file_server {
			root ./cmd
			browse
			import snippet_hide_common
			hide cobra* main.go
		}
	}
}
```

